Question

Which graph shows a 682\(^\circ\) angle in standard position?


Answerlist

  • A
  • B
  • C
  • D
  • E
  • F
  • G
  • H

Solution

The given angle is 682\(^\circ\). The angle is positive, so the angle rotates counterclockwise.

Notice if we divide 682 by 360 we get 1 with a remainder of 322. So, rotate 1 full times and then also rotate by 322\(^\circ\).

Notice that 322\(^\circ\) is between 270\(^\circ\) and 360\(^\circ\), so it’ll need between 3 and 4 quarter turns after the 1 full turns (all counterclockwise). That puts the terminal side in quadrant 4 (quadrant IV).
